reet Maintenance Worker I STARTING SALARY: $15.37/hr.</p><p>+ benefitsDEPARTMENT: Street/Fleet CLOSING DATE: October 19, 2016 - 5 p.m.Definition:Under specific instruction, performs a variety of semi-skilled and/orskilled labor in construction, maintenance, and repair services.</p><p>Thisposition must work well independently and with teams, while providingexcellent, respectful customer service and human relations skills, whichsupport the City of Brighton s mission and values.</p><p>This is an entry-levelposition which performs semi-skilled labor in the construction, maintenanceand repair of street, sidewalk, storm drain and other City facilities,as well as traffic painting and street signage under general supervision.Example of Duties:Respond to on-site requests and inquiries from public; maintain daily worklog; identify equipment needs for projects; utilize proper safetyprecautions for all work performed; assist other departments in majorprojects, as necessary; work varying shifts and schedules as needed andrequired by supervisor.</p><p>Some overtime will be occasionally required andassigned as necessary.</p><p>Responsibilities and duties may include, but are notlimited to, the following: Works as part of a street maintenance crew;shovels and spreads asphalt and asphalt base in the patching, repairing andreconstructing of streets; use concrete cutting and breaking equipment;operates a jackhammer; form, pour and finishes concrete; constructconcrete forms and perform rough carpentry work; perform snow removal dutiesby operating truck-mounted snow plows, graders and sand spreader; cuts,installs and sets storm drain pipes to proper grades; inspects and clearsobstructions from storm drains; paint traffic control markings such ascrosswalks, lane stripes and parking zones on City streets and curbs;install sign posts, signs and reflective traffic markers; spread and packgravel in City alleys and roadways; identify equipment needs for eachassigned project; operate construction equipment such as tandem axle dumptrucks, rollers, front loaders, street sweepers, and power tools suchas compressors, jack hammers, paint sprayers, sandblasters, concretesaws and sewer rodders in a variety of construction, maintenance and capitalimprovement projects; utilize proper safety precautions related to all workperformed; assists in construction of parks, small lakes and similarfacilities.</p><p>Assist other departments in major projects; install streetbarricades and cones prior to the performance of street repair activities;direRequired Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities:Knowledge of: Methods, techniques and tools and the operationalcharacteristics of mechanical equipment used in construction, repair andmaintenance; uses, safety practices and purposes of general hand tools andlight equipment; operation of a two-way radio; safe work practices.</p><p>Skillin: Maintaining records and laws; safe and lawful operation of a motorvehicle.</p><p>Ability to: Learn to perform semi-skilled and skilled tasks in avariety of construction and maintenance activities; perform semi-skilledmaintenance, construction and repair work in the area of work assigned;operate a variety of vehicular and stationary mechanical equipment in a safeand effective manner in routine situations; use and operate hand tools,mechanical equipment, and power tools and equipment required for the work ina safe and efficient manner; perform heavy manual labor; perform on-callduty as required by department; read and interpret basic maps andblueprints, if required; work independently in the absence ofsupervision, whenEducation and Training:One year of experience performing construction, repair and/or maintenanceduties is desirable.</p><p>Possession of valid, Colorado driver s license required.Special Requirements:12 months to obtain CDL Class A license with tanker endorsement.</p><p>BilingualEnglish/Spanish preferred.Apply online at or at 500 S.</p><p>4th Avenue, Brighton, CO80601(Phone fax )EQUAL OPPO